  <description>Plants forming dense colonies, 0.3–6 dm, superficially rhizom-atous; twigs yellow-green, reddish green, or reddish brown, terete to somewhat angled, finely puberulent or, rarely, glabrous.  Leaf blades green, usually oblanceolate, sometimes obovate or narrowly elliptic, 10–30 × 3–12 mm, margins usually serrulate from apex to at least mid blade, surfaces usually glandular abaxially, usually glabrous adaxially.  Flowers: calyx pale green, lobes vestigial, glabrous; corolla white, white with pink striping, or pink, cylindric-urceolate to globose, 4–7 × 3–5 mm, thin, glaucous; filaments glabrous.  Berries usually blue, glaucous, rarely dull black, 5–9 mm diam.  Seeds ca. 1 mm.  2n = 24.</description>
  <phenology>Flowering late spring–mid summer</phenology>
